					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Edward McPherson</h4>
												<p>Edward McPherson is the author of <em>Buster Keaton: Tempest in a Flat Hat, The Backwash Squeeze and Other Improbable Feats,</em> and <em>The History of the Future: American Essays</em> (forthcoming May 2017). He has written for the <em>American Scholar, Epoch, the New York Times Magazine, the Paris Review, Salon, the Southern Review,</em> and <em>Tin House</em>, among others. He received a Pushcart Prize for his short story “Telref,” which appeared in the Spring 2014 issue of the <em>Gettysburg Review</em>, and the Gulf Coast Prize in fiction. He teaches creative writing at Washington University in Saint Louis.</p>
					</div>
